{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011BAH9Yk1HJbAWRUnFawaL4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile the findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI found all the requested implementations in the backend code. Here's what each one does:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **`insertReferralLink` method** (db.ts, lines 808-815)\n\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralLink(referrerWallet, refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_links (referrer_wallet, referee_wallet)\n    VALUES (${referrerWallet}, ${refereeWallet})\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n},\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Creates a referral link record linking a referrer wallet to a referee wallet. Throws on duplicate referee (unique constraint).\n\n---\n\n## 2. **`getReferralLinkByReferee` method** (db.ts, lines 817-822)\n\n```typescript\nasync getReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_links WHERE referee_wallet = ${refereeWallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n},\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Fetches the referral link record for a specific referee wallet. Returns the first (and only) match, or `undefined` if the referee has no referrer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. **`getReferralCodeByCode` method** (db.ts, lines 787-792)\n\n```typescript\nasync getReferralCodeByCode(code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_codes WHERE code = ${code}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n},\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Looks up a referral code record by the code string (e.g., \"my-code\"). Returns `undefined` if the code doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n## 4. **JWT Validation & Wallet Extraction Pattern** \n\nThe pattern used across all routes is consistent:\n\n### Middleware Setup (jwt-auth.ts, lines 20-59):\n- Middleware `createJwtAuthMiddleware` extracts the Bearer token from the `Authorization` header\n- Uses `jwtVerify()` from `jose` library to validate HS256 signature\n- Extracts the wallet from `payload.sub` claim\n- Sets it on context: `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)` (AppEnv type-safe)\n- Returns 401 if missing/invalid\n\n### Route Usage Pattern (all routes):\n```typescript\n// In any route handler:\nconst wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\nif (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n```\n\n**Examples in the codebase:**\n\n- **referral.ts line 25** (POST /code endpoint):\n  ```typescript\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n  if (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  ```\n\n- **profile.ts line 35** (GET /transactions endpoint):\n  ```typescript\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n  if (!wallet) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **profile.ts line 93** (POST /confirm-tx endpoint):\n  ```typescript\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n  if (!wallet) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  }\n  ```\n\n### Type Safety:\n- `AppEnv` type (hono-env.ts) defines `Variables: { wallet: string }`\n- Allows TypeScript to type-check `c.get(\"wallet\")` as returning `string | undefined`\n\n---\n\n## File References:\n\n- **db.ts implementations**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n- **Route patterns**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`, `/routes/profile.ts`\n- **JWT middleware**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- **Type definitions**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a416faf147e316171 (use SendMessage with to: 'a416faf147e316171' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59130\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 40080</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d179094-b1ae-4405-8e43-449089b7a949","uuid":"b1f8888d-61c2-4cac-aae0-123ba7b0c8ba","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:59:31.773Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and show me these specific things in the backend code at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/:\n1. The `insertReferralLink` method implementation in db.ts\n2. The `getReferralLinkByReferee` method implementation in db.ts\n3. The `getReferralCodeByCode` method implementation in db.ts\n4. How other route files validate JWT and get the wallet from context (look at the pattern in existing routes)\n\nShow the actual code for each. Be thorough - search for \"insertReferralLink\", \"getReferralLinkByReferee\", \"getReferralCodeByCode\" in db.ts.","agentId":"a416faf147e316171","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile the findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI found all the requested implementations in the backend code. Here's what each one does:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **`insertReferralLink` method** (db.ts, lines 808-815)\n\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralLink(referrerWallet, refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_links (referrer_wallet, referee_wallet)\n    VALUES (${referrerWallet}, ${refereeWallet})\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n},\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Creates a referral link record linking a referrer wallet to a referee wallet. Throws on duplicate referee (unique constraint).\n\n---\n\n## 2. **`getReferralLinkByReferee` method** (db.ts, lines 817-822)\n\n```typescript\nasync getReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_links WHERE referee_wallet = ${refereeWallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n},\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Fetches the referral link record for a specific referee wallet. Returns the first (and only) match, or `undefined` if the referee has no referrer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. **`getReferralCodeByCode` method** (db.ts, lines 787-792)\n\n```typescript\nasync getReferralCodeByCode(code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_codes WHERE code = ${code}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n},\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Looks up a referral code record by the code string (e.g., \"my-code\"). Returns `undefined` if the code doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n## 4. **JWT Validation & Wallet Extraction Pattern** \n\nThe pattern used across all routes is consistent:\n\n### Middleware Setup (jwt-auth.ts, lines 20-59):\n- Middleware `createJwtAuthMiddleware` extracts the Bearer token from the `Authorization` header\n- Uses `jwtVerify()` from `jose` library to validate HS256 signature\n- Extracts the wallet from `payload.sub` claim\n- Sets it on context: `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)` (AppEnv type-safe)\n- Returns 401 if missing/invalid\n\n### Route Usage Pattern (all routes):\n```typescript\n// In any route handler:\nconst wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\nif (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n```\n\n**Examples in the codebase:**\n\n- **referral.ts line 25** (POST /code endpoint):\n  ```typescript\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n  if (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  ```\n\n- **profile.ts line 35** (GET /transactions endpoint):\n  ```typescript\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n  if (!wallet) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **profile.ts line 93** (POST /confirm-tx endpoint):\n  ```typescript\n  const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n  if (!wallet) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n  }\n  ```\n\n### Type Safety:\n- `AppEnv` type (hono-env.ts) defines `Variables: { wallet: string }`\n- Allows TypeScript to type-check `c.get(\"wallet\")` as returning `string | undefined`\n\n---\n\n## File References:\n\n- **db.ts implementations**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n- **Route patterns**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`, `/routes/profile.ts`\n- **JWT middleware**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- **Type definitions**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`"}],"totalDurationMs":40080,"totalTokens":59130,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1087,"cache_read_input_tokens":56976,"output_tokens":1060,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1087},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
